parameters: Heya kid, just having a look-around?
Nice find, the first few issues are hard to come by.
If someone was able to get the whole collection together
they'd be able to make a lot of money off 'em.
Hey kid, you gonna buy anything or just browsing?
This way, I know the owner.
Good Morrow, Lady Leigh of the Sacred Ash! And how might I,
a humble merchant, be of assistance today?
Keeper of the enchanted realm of tomes!
...I’m \N[001] by the way. Is there a gas leak in here,
Who’s the killjoy casual over here? By the way, this
isn’t a damn library. You open it, you bought it.
Easy there, “Scary Gary”. This is my brother, \N[001].
I'm just popping in to grab my CoK notes,
I left them here after my last game.
COK... That’s the fantasy role playing
"Game”?! Calamity of Kingdoms is no mere game.
It is a test of one’s own imagination, intuition,
All that with little plastic dudes and weird looking dice?
Gary, this is why we hardly see any business.
You can come on a... A bit strong, sometimes.
Aw hell, Ashley. You’re right. Forgive me, man.
I’m passionate about the stuff in this shop. I have to
remind myself on occasion to ease people into these hobbies.
It’s all good, dude. There must be something to
the game if you two are that excited about it.
Well I get that it’s not for everyone,
but there’s something special when you’re with
a group of friends roleplaying together.
Everyone has fantasies in their head,
and this gives you a chance to act it out in a fun way.
She’s right. You can slay horrific abominations...
Don’t be vulgar you two. But yeah, pretty much anything
you want so long as it follows the Game Master’s campaign.
It’s like the host who plans out the entire adventure,
with all the unexpected twists and turns.
My notes are back here, right?
Can’t run a game without that monster, o’course.
Geez, Ash. Do you really need all that to play?
I’m thorough, I'll just say that...
Hey, so... We're actually a player short for the game - we
had a third but he dropped out randomly... Would you
wanna sit in, see if you like it?
That’s the attitude I like to hear! Tell you what, since
you’re new, I’ll let you pick from one of the new miniatures
that just came in last shipment. Go ahead, CHOOSE YOUR FATE!
Hmm... I guess I’ll pick that one.
It’s like a crafty spellcaster that specializes in
Subtlety over raw strength, that kind of thing.
< I already have plenty of practice swaying people anyway.>
Great! Happy to see you getting into the spirit.
Our party already has a healer and a fighter,
so this should round us out quite nicely.
Oof - forgot how heavy this thing was. Anyway, thanks Gary.
You kids have a good time. \N[001], nice meeting ya!

No, I didn’t see the movie, and I don’t care to.
Umm... See I just thought that...
I’ve heard this exact same conversation a hundred times
with a thousand fanboys bitching about adaptations.
I DON’T CARE. Now will that be everything?
Ashley! How ya been? And \N[001] is back too, I see.
What, that guy? Pfft, he ordered expensive statues and
then decided he didn’t want them anymore. I don’t forget
Ah-ah! “Wise”, not old. I’ll outlive you all, just wait.
So young lady, what can I do for you? Perusing my wares,
or are you here for the card game in the back? Barbara
and Charles are playing right now.
Ooooh but I can’t - I was supposed to...
Hahaha... Go say hi to them. Do you want me to grab your
books for you? I’ll meet you back there when I’m done.
For real? I’ll be really quick, I promise!
Try not to get obsessed over another hobby!
Mind helping me out, Gary? You gotta know what she likes.
Haven’t pulled her stuff yet, it’s still on the shelf.
Let me just look up what came in this week.
She has three issues on order. Our winners are:
“Wrath of The Realms”, “Saur Soldiers”, and “Chrono Cabbie”.
Ya get all of that, Kid?
Go forth and complete this quest, young warrior!
At least try to roll with the bit once, man...
Oh! Uh, “Verily, master wizard”! How was that?
Uh... It's called, uh- Brother Sister.
Oh cool, is it like a brother sister crime-fighting
Uhhh... It's about a brother and a sister that...
Ooookay... Well, have fun I guess...
Hey, this is getting really good, leave me alone please...
Excuse me, you know where I could
find the latest issue of “Chrono Cabbie”?
Got the last one right here! Going to flip
it online for a quick buck because of a printing error.
Oh... Uh, look guy - could you do me a solid?
It’s for my sister, and it would really make her happy.
Depends. Do you have three hundred dollars?
Three hun- Fuck that! That’s robbery!
Tough, that’s the estimated value. Now get out of my face.
<What do I want to do here?>
C’mon, man. There’s no way anyone is going to buy it
for that much. Be a bro, and help make my sisters day.
I... Suppose you are right. Here, take it. My mom would
kill me if she found out I was buying stuff here anyway...
Give me the fucking book, you're too old to be
collecting comics. Go home, get rid of your collection
and start looking for a job or something.
I... Huh? Okay... Here you go, man... I gotta get home...
Now let’s see how she’s doing over by the card tables.>
This latest chapter is really good...
Oh, this is that new comic - Espectra. Ghost-fighting
vigilante cat burglar... Weird premise, but the main
I should ask the clerk about this, see if I can get a copy.
<Shouldn't bug them until I have all the books...>

Hey guys. What are you playing?
\N[001], our newest party member! Good seeing you again!
I was just showing your sister my BaLS!
... You want to run that by me again, Chuck?
It’s this cool new card game released called
“Beasts and Legendary Sorcerers! Gary gave Chuckie and Babs
first dibs on the card packs.
It’sh amazshing! You play a shorsherer card,
then play theesh monshter cardsh to shummon!
So... It’s like CoK, only with trading cards?
Oh no, nothing like that. A game within a game?
But from what I can tell, it’s a hoot nonetheless.
If you enjoy CoK, it’s natural to like BaLS too!
Babs was just about to open up her first card pack.
Nice! You got some rare ones already -
Helhala of The Damned, and an Ember Octopus! Lucky...
Thish ish the greatesht day of my life..!
Do you two want to stick around a
while, maybe learn the game a bit?
We're having a family-day thing today.
I can’t say no to my little bro!
Not a problem! I’m sure we can play
with my BaLS some other time.
HEY I GOT YOUR BOOKS, ASH!
Let’s go pay for them, shall we?
Sure. Love you guys! See you next time!
Think so. Though I gotta tell you, Gary, this one might be
worth some money. Some guy said it was selling hot online.
Damn speculators, they ruin the hobby for everyone. I could
care less about what it flips for, the story is what really
matters. But I appreciate you being upfront about it.
That’s why I like selling to customers like your sister
here. She actually gives a crap about the characters.
Well how could I not be crazy about Chrono Cabbie?!
Like, take last issue for example when Tulip-
LALALALA! I’m not listening! I haven’t
caught up on my reading, Ashley!
Gary, you need to catch up! Who else am I going
to talk about this with? You won’t watch the show!
How could you not know about the show!?
It’s only been the best science fiction drama to
I haven’t been watching much TV
Good?! It... Hold on, that gives me a fantastic idea.
I know what we’re doing the rest of the day -
Gary, ring us up. My brother NEEDS
Why don’t I pay for your books this time?
This way you can save up some cash for that
card game thing your friends like.
I know I don’t, but I want to.
You’re doing enough for me lately.
Well... Okay! Thank you, and I
promise I’ll pay you back later.
Here you go, Gary. I’ll be back to splurge on some
more stuff once I have the pocket change for it.
Here you go, Gary. I’ll be back to splurge on some
more stuff once I have the pocket change for it.
You two are always welcome inside my lair.
You really like this series, huh?
I don’t “like” Chrono Cabbie, I LIVE Chrono Cabbie. It’s
second only to CoK for me, and pretty damn popular outside
nerd social groups. You seriously haven’t heard of it?
Can’t say that I have, no.
Maybe I should check it out sometime.
Not “sometime”, today. We’re binge watching as much as we
possibly can until we pass out. I NEED to see you
experience this, and talk about it afterwards.
We can watch every episode when we get home. How bout it?
<I can’t remember the last time I saw Ashley excited over a
TV show like this. Even if I don’t end up liking it,
spending time with her should be enough.>
Why not? For you to hype it up this much
it must be worth at least one episode.
